Module com.project2.project2fpoe
Package com.project2.project2fpoe.model

Class Sudoku

java.lang.Object
com.project2.project2fpoe.model.Sudoku
public class Sudoku extends Object
Sudoku class to represent the Sudoku game logic. This class handles the generation of the Sudoku board, validation of moves, and checking if the Sudoku is solved.

  • Constructor Details

    • Sudoku

      public Sudoku()
      Constructor to initialize the Sudoku board. The board is a 6x6 grid initialized with zeros.

  • Method Details

    • generatePlayableBoard

      public void generatePlayableBoard()
      Method to generate a playable Sudoku board. This method fills the board with numbers and checks if the board is resolvable.

    • fillBlocksWithTwoNumbers

      private void fillBlocksWithTwoNumbers()
      Method to fill blocks of the Sudoku board with two numbers. This method randomly selects two cells in each block and fills them with numbers.

    • isResolvable

      private boolean isResolvable()
      Method to check if the Sudoku board is resolvable. This method creates a copy of the board and attempts to solve it.
      Returns:
      true if the board is resolvable, false otherwise

    • clearBoard

      private void clearBoard()
      Method to clear the Sudoku board. This method sets all cells in the board to zero.

    • getBoard

      public List<List<Integer>> getBoard()

    • setCell

      public boolean setCell(int row, int col, int value)
      Method to set a cell in the Sudoku board. This method checks if the move is valid before placing the number.
      Parameters:
      row - the row index of the cell
      col - the column index of the cell
      value - the value to place in the cell
      Returns:
      true if the move is valid and successful, false otherwise

    • isValidMove

      public boolean isValidMove(List<List<Integer>> board, int row, int col, int value)
      Method to check if a move is valid in the Sudoku board. This method checks if the number can be placed in the specified cell without violating Sudoku rules.
      Parameters:
      board - the Sudoku board
      row - the row index of the cell
      col - the column index of the cell
      value - the value to place in the cell
      Returns:
      true if the move is valid, false otherwise

    • isSolved

      public boolean isSolved()
      Method to check if the Sudoku board is solved. This method checks if all cells are filled and if the Sudoku rules are satisfied.
      Returns:
      true if the Sudoku is solved, false otherwise

    • printBoard

      public void printBoard()
      Method to print the Sudoku board. This method prints the board to the console for debugging purposes.

    • printBoardCopy

      public void printBoardCopy()
      Method to print the copied Sudoku board. This method prints the copied board to the console for debugging purposes.

    • solve

      public boolean solve()
      Method to solve the Sudoku board using backtracking. This method attempts to fill the board with numbers recursively.
      Returns:
      true if the Sudoku is solved, false otherwise
